ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
0 = Self/subject; 1 = Mother; 2 = Father; 3 = Other primary caregiver; 4 = Other (describe); -9 = Missing value

1 = ABA/discrete trial/Lovaas/intensive early intervention; 2 = Occupational therapy; 3 = Physical therapy; 4 = Speech therapy; 5 = Counseling/psychological services for child; 6 = Play therapy; 7 = Music therapy; 8 = Auditory integration training; 9 = TEACCH; 10 = Developmental play therapy (Hanen, RDI); 11 = Social skills training; 12 = Special education; 13 = Parent-child socialization/skill building support; 14 = Recreational sports for child; 15 = Typical class; 16 = Home program (not ABA); 17 = Biomedical/nutritional; 18 = Parenting class/seminar; 19 = Counseling/psychological services for parent; 20 = Parent-child recreation; 21 = Integrated/blended class; 22 = Home school; -9 = Missing Value
1 = Hours per week or event; 2 = Other (describe); -9 = Missing value
1 = Specialist; 2 = Paraprofessional; 3 = Untrained parent/volunteer; -9 = Missing value
